    title: "The Gravity Switch",
    author: "Khyati Srivastava",
    slug: "the-gravity-switch",
    category: "Sci-Fi",
    emoji: "🌍",
    excerpt: "Two rival inventors flip the wrong switch and accidentally turn off gravity for an entire school.",
    created_at: "2026-05-27T00:00:00Z",
    body: "<p style='color:#6a4b8f;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:18px'>By Khyati Srivastava</p><p>Dev and Lina were the two best inventors at Northgate School, and they could not stand each other. Each was sure their science fair project would beat the other's.</p><p>Dev built a machine he called the Gravity Switch, meant to make objects a little lighter so movers could carry heavy furniture. Lina laughed and said it would never work.</p><p>To prove her wrong, Dev cranked the dial all the way up the morning of the fair. The machine hummed, sparked, and let out a deep thump. Then every pencil, backpack, and student in the gymnasium began to float gently toward the ceiling.</p><p>Children drifted like balloons, giggling and shrieking. Papers swirled. Lina floated past Dev, no longer laughing.</p><p>We have to turn it off together, Dev shouted. The reverse switch is across the room and I cannot reach it alone.</p><p>So the two rivals worked as a team for the first time. Lina pushed off a wall and floated toward Dev. He caught her hand and flung her toward the machine. She grabbed the lever, and Dev called out the exact settings to undo the field.</p><p>With a soft sigh, gravity returned. Everyone settled to the floor, breathless and grinning.</p><p>The judges were so amazed that they gave Dev and Lina a joint prize, on one condition: they had to keep the machine switched off.</p><p>From that day on, the two inventors built everything together. They had learned that the smartest minds rise higher when they stop pulling against each other.</p>",
