    title: "The Substitute Teacher's Secret",
    author: "Khyati Srivastava",
    slug: "the-substitute-teachers-secret",
    category: "Comedy",
    emoji: "🎭",
    excerpt: "Mr. Finch, the substitute everyone dreads, has a reputation for being impossibly strict — and an equally impossible secret talent nobody expects.",
    created_at: "2026-10-20T15:00:00Z",
    body: "<p style='color:#6a4b8f;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:18px'>By Khyati Srivastava</p><p>Every class dreaded a Mr. Finch day. He wore the same grey cardigan, spoke in the same flat monotone, and enforced silent independent reading with the grim determination of a man who had never once, in his entire career, cracked a smile.</p><p>Room 14 groaned collectively when they saw his name on the whiteboard. What they didn't know, because nobody had ever stuck around after the bell to find out, was that Mr. Finch spent every weekend as the lead singer of a moderately successful ska band called The Chalkboard Riot, complete with a trombone section and a small but devoted following at three different bars downtown.</p><p>The truth came out entirely by accident, when a student's older sister recognized him mid-performance and posted the video before realizing what she'd done. By Monday, the whole school had seen Mr. Finch, cardigan nowhere in sight, belting out a horn-heavy anthem to a cheering crowd with his eyes closed and his whole soul on the stage.</p><p>He arrived Monday morning expecting mockery and got, instead, a room of stunned respect and one kid working up the nerve to ask if the band needed a trumpet player. Mr. Finch allowed himself, for the first documented time in Room 14's history, the very smallest smile. \"Silent reading first,\" he said. \"We'll talk trumpets after.\"</p>",
