    body: "<p style='color:#6a4b8f;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:18px'>By Khyati Srivastava</p><p>Nobody claps for the hundredth free throw,<br>the missed note fixed alone in a practice room,<br>the third rewrite of a paragraph<br>that no one else will ever see or read.</p><p>Nobody claps for showing up again<br>the day after you failed at something small,<br>for lacing up the shoes when it's still dark,<br>for trying, one more time, before you fall.</p><p>But somewhere in the hundredth quiet try,<br>the shot starts curving where you meant it to.<br>Somewhere in the rewrite no one saw,<br>the sentence finally sounds like it is true.</p><p>So here's to every round no one applauds,<br>the practice hours nobody's here to see —<br>they're not the warm-up for some later day.<br>They're where you're quietly becoming who you'll be.</p>",
